_source.title: Literacy Rate
_source.description: Total Literates per 100 People Above 6 Years of Age
_source.formula: (Male Literates + Female Literates)/(Total Population - Population Age 0-6)

_source.title: Gender Literacy Ratio
_source.description: Female Literates per 100 Male Literates
_source.formula: (Female Literacy Rate/Male Literacy Rate)*100

_source.title: Female Literacy Rate
_source.description: Female Literates per 100 Females Above 6 Years of Age
_source.formula: (Female Literates/(Total Females - Females Age 0-6))*100

_source.title: Male Literacy Rate
_source.description: Male Literates per 100 Males Above 6 Years of Age
_source.formula: (Male Literates/(Total Males - Males Age 0-6))*100

_source.title: Decadal Gains in Literacy (Z-Score)
_source.description: Number of standard deviations from average gain in literacy for the State.  Positive values indicate above average gains while negative values indicate less than average gains.
_source.formula: Z-score (Literacy Rate 2011 / Literacy Rate 2001)

_source.title: Age Ratio (0-6)
_source.description: Number of Children in 0-6 Age Group per 1000 Population
_source.formula: (Population in Age group 0-6/Total Population)*1000

_source.title: Main Worker Rate
_source.description: Main Workers (Workers employed more than 6 months of the reference period) per 100 Workers
_source.formula: Main Workers/Total Workers

_source.title: Main Worker Rate for Females
_source.description: Female Main Workers (Workers employed more than 6 months of the reference period) per 100 Female Workers
_source.formula: Main Female Workers/Total Female Workers

_source.title: Main Worker Rate for Males
_source.description: Male Main Workers (Workers employed more than 6 months of the reference period) per 100 Male Workers
_source.formula: Main Male Workers/Total Male Workers

_source.title: Main Worker Rate Gender Ratio
_source.description: Ratio of Female Main Workers to Male Main Workers
_source.formula: Main Worker Rate Female/Main Worker Rate Male

_source.title: Average Household Size
_source.description: Average Number of People per Household
_source.formula: Total Population/Number of Households

_source.title: Decadal Urbanization (Z-Score)
_source.description: Number of standard deviations from average urbanization for the State.  Positive values indicate above average gains while negative values indicate less than average gains.
_source.formula: Z-score (Urban Percent 2011/Urban Percent 2001)

_source.title: Urbanization Ratio
_source.description: Ratio of population living in settlements of size 100,000 or more to population living in settlements of size 10,000 or Less
_source.formula: (Total Population > 100000)/(Total Population < 10000)

_source.title: Urban Percent
_source.description: % of Population Living in Settlements of Size 50,000 or More
_source.formula: (Total Population > 50000)/Total Population

_source.title: Industrial Worker Rate
_source.description: Percent of Total Workers in Non-Agricultural Industries
_source.formula: ((Main Workers in Household Industries + Main Other Workers) / Total Workers) * 100

_source.title: Emp in Construction (45)
_source.description: % of Total Workers Employed in Construction out of all Workers (excluding workers engaged in primary cultivation)(NIC F45)
_source.formula: People Employed in [Industry name]/Total People Employed

_source.title: Decadal Industrialization (Z-Score)
_source.description: Number of standard deviations from average decadal increase in industrialization for the State.  Industrialization is determined by the fraction of people employed in non-agricultural activities.  Positive values indicate above average gains while negative values indicate less than average gains.
_source.formula: Z-score (Industrial Worker Rate 2011/Industrial Worker Rate 2001)

_source.title: Population Density
_source.description: Population per Square Km
_source.formula: Total Population / Land area

_source.title: Agriculture Worker Rate
_source.description: Percent of Total Workers Employed in Agriculture
_source.formula: ((Main Cultivators + Main Agricultural Labourers)/Total Workers) * 100

_source.title: Decadal Migration
_source.description: Number of standard deviations from the average increase in population for the State or the Z-Score of the log (Population 2011/Population 2001).Positive values indicate inward migration while negative values indicate outward migration.
_source.formula: Z-score (Total Population 2011/Total Population 2001)
